init_text: Humans once wielded formidable magical power. But with over 7 billion of us on the planet now, Mana has spread far too thinly to have any effect. When hostile aliens reduce humanity to a mere fraction, the survivors discover an old power has begun to reawaken once again.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The steady hum of the power generators, the quiet conversation of her fellow survivors, and a familiar loping thump as Herman ran by outside.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: She got up and opened her door, which was something of a minor accomplishment these days.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Even the impromptu prosthetics Morgan had rigged up herself were more trouble than they were worth.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Something he said was like a really strong tingle, but didn't hurt.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: From there it was a mad dash back to the bunker, followed by days of hushed talk and whispered rumors.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: And they started feeling things too.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: She steeled herself and pushed the door open, glad to get out of her tiny room.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The walk to the lab wasn't a long one (unless you were missing a leg, of course), but it felt like an eternity

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Whatever the reason, Morgan was grateful not to have to worry about any other distractions.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: She didn't even need to touch it - the feeling was already coming.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: as her hand connected, and a pulse of light flowed out.
